    <!--
        ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        HUD ICON GEOMETRY  —  24×24 viewbox, STROKED (not filled)
        ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

        Every path here is drawn as an OUTLINE by HudIcon: 1.5px stroke, flat caps,
        miter joins. That is the whole point of the set — MaterialDesign's PackIcon
        geometry is *filled* and *rounded*, which fights the brutalist style.

        Rules for authoring/adding a glyph:
          • Straight segments and hard corners. Prefer 45°/90°. No curves unless the
            shape is meaningless without one (clock face, radar sweep).
          • Keep to the 24×24 grid, roughly a 2..22 safe area so the 1.5px stroke
            doesn't clip at the edges.
          • Do NOT close a path (Z) unless the shape really is a closed loop — a
            stray Z adds a visible diagonal.
          • Design at the intended size. These render at 13–19px, so anything with
            more than ~8 segments turns to mush.

        Naming mirrors the MaterialDesign Kind we replaced, so call sites map 1:1.
    -->

    <!-- ── Nav / structure ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->

    <!-- ViewDashboard: four unequal panes -->
